HEADWORD: Tylosis
<hw>Ty*lo"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tyloses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>ty`los</grk> a lump, knot.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An
intrusion of one vegetable cell into the cavity of another, sometimes
forming there an irregular mass of cells.</def>
<rj><au>Goodale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
